<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4858] hbase-site.xml example in quickstart doesn&apos;t work in Linux</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4858</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Under Linux with OpenJDK 1.6, using a &lt;a href=&quot;file:///XX&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;file:///XX&lt;/a&gt; URL in the config file creates a directory called &apos;file:&apos; in the hbase root directory. If I use a standard Unix absolute path, it works as expected. This may work on other platforms, but it would be good to add a note in the example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;?xml version=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;1.0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;?&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;?xml-stylesheet type=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;text/xsl&quot;&lt;/span&gt; href=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;configuration.xsl&quot;&lt;/span&gt;?&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;property&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;hbase.rootdir&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;!-- Depending on your platform, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; may create a &apos;file:&apos; directory
         in hbase home instead of the desired behavior. Try using a standard
         platform specific absolute path instead. --&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;file:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;///DIRECTORY/hbase&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;  &amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;java version &quot;1.6.0_23&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
OpenJDK Runtime Environment (IcedTea6 1.11pre) (6b23~pre11-1)&lt;br/&gt;
OpenJDK Client VM (build 20.0-b11, mixed mode, sharing)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
